# Implement Delivery Executor

> **Status: stub — implementation pending.** Contract only. Consolidates
> the greenfield Arrow-path patterns from
> `narrative-connectors/.claude/skills/migrate-connector-to-arrow`
> (`Arrow<Slug>ConnectorParser`, `Arrow<Slug>AudienceFileReader`,
> `FileDeliveryMetrics`) so new connectors start on the Arrow path rather
> than the legacy JSON path.

## Purpose

Implement the executor that reads a materialized audience and delivers it
to the partner via `/implement-partner-client`. New connectors are built
directly on the Arrow Dataset path (`ArrowConnectorReader.readBatches`),
skipping the legacy JSON parse path entirely.

Phase: **service**.

## Inputs (from connector-spec.yaml)

- `delivery.path` (arrow for new connectors), `delivery.update_model`,
  `delivery.ttl`, `delivery.optout_handling`.
- `identifier_groups[]` → the bound field parsers and narrative_id routing.
- `partner_api.batch_limit` + concurrency targets → batching and JVM
  heap/direct-memory sizing.

## Outputs

- `Arrow<Slug>ConnectorParser`, `Arrow<Slug>AudienceFileReader`,
  `<Slug>ConnectorConfig`.
- `FileDeliveryMetrics` + reporter; the rewritten executor(s);
  `RuntimeConfig` + `ARROW_BATCH_SIZE` wiring.

## Human gates

- Local code — actual delivery to the partner is a `/deploy-connector` +
  `/verify-connector` concern, gated there.
- **Correctness rule (carried from the Arrow migration):** delivered
  `total_rows` / `total_identifiers` must match the expected baseline
  exactly. A parser-count mismatch is a correctness regression, not a
  fix-forward — surfaced at verify time.

